# UI Layout Standards
> Authority: See authority.mdc

【VALIDATE】 Use Tailwind-first approach with minimal custom CSS, apply `!important` modifiers when CSS conflicts occur, implement responsive grid progression, use glass morphism effects, maintain zero-scroll viewport design on mobile.

## Core Standards

### CSS Architecture
- Use Tailwind utilities first, custom CSS only when necessary
- When spacing/layout classes don't work: 【STOP】 check for CSS conflicts, then apply `!important` modifiers
- Avoid CSS variables that duplicate Tailwind functionality
- Keep custom CSS minimal (animations, unique effects only)

### Responsive Grid Progression
`grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4` - Progressive 1→2→3→4 columns 【PLAN】

### Glass Morphism Design
`bg-gradient-to-br from-white/95 to-gray-50/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-gray-200/60 shadow-lg`

### Component Standards
- Rounding: `rounded-xl` (primary), `rounded-full` (badges)
- Animations: `transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-1`
- Touch targets: Minimum `py-4 px-5` for buttons
- Zero-scroll mobile: Fit 100vh viewport, use horizontal scrolling for cards

## Example
```html
<div class="!p-8 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 !gap-6">
  <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white/95 to-gray-50/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-gray-200/60 shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-1">
  </div>
</div>
```